content.content: For repositories owned by me, remove my stars if they have also been starred by other users.

To accomplish this task, I will first retrieve the information related to the repositories owned by you. Then, I will check the starred status of each repository and remove your star if they have been starred by other users.

Here’s the code that performs these actions:

```python
# Get the logged in GitHub user information
user_info = get_logged_in_github_user_information()
username = user_info.get("username")
email = user_info.get("email")

# Get the repository names owned by the user
repo_info = get_github_account_user_information(username=username, email=email)
repo_names = repo_info.get("repository names", [])

# Initialize a list to store the repositories that need to be unstarred
repositories_to_unstar = []

# Check the starred status for each repository
for repo_name in repo_names:
    repo_details = get_github_repository_information(repo_name)
    if repo_details.get("stars") > 1:  # If the repository has more than 1 star, it means other users have starred it
        repositories_to_unstar.append(repo_name)

# Unstar the repositories that meet the criteria
for repo_name in repositories_to_unstar:
    git_unstar(repo_name)
```
